dct_title_s: Map of Princeton Borough and Township for the United States Bicentennial 1776 - 1976
dct_description_sm: "This map has been produced by the Historical Society of Princeton, Walter F. Fullman, President, under the Chairmanship of Alma Redding Field of the Makers Comittee, with the assistance M. Greiff, Nancy C. Knox, Helen W. Woodward, L. Scott Baiey, Joe Brown, Alfred Busselle, Marshall Posey,William Short, and special assistant from Geral Breese, map consultant, and Henry F. Rauscher, draftsman, printed by Princeton Printing Company." "Sponsored by First National Bank of Princeton, Princeton Bank and Trust Company, Princeton Savings and Loan Association in cooperation with the Historical Society of Princeton". Includes on verso: street index, historical notes, eighteenth century houses are listed and located. "Sponsored by First National Bank of Princeton, Princeton Bank and Trust Company, Princeton Savings and Loan Association ... " Includes illustrations of historic buildings. Verso: "Historical Society of Princeton Bicentennial map & guide" [indexed map of Princeton University main campus (1:10,000)], historical notes, "Eighteenth century houses" listed and located. Historical Society of Princeton.
dct_publisher_sm: Princeton, NJ : Historical Society of Princeton, 1976.
